      "title": "Comparison and Recommendation",
      "content_type": "table",
      "purpose": "Provide a side-by-side comparison of the GRAT and CRAT across key planning dimensions: estate tax savings, wealth transfer to children, charitable component, net estate after each strategy, performance dependence, and mortality risk. Include a comparison table. Analyse the different performance benchmarks — the GRAT depends on beating the §7520 rate while the CRAT pays a fixed annuity regardless of investment performance. Quantify the mortality risk for this client's age and contrast with the CRAT's absence of equivalent risk. Frame the client's marital status and combined exemption as a material factor in the estate-tax analysis. Address wealth-replacement considerations where the CRAT does not transfer wealth to heirs. Close with a recommendation consistent with the executive summary, explaining which strategy is primary and which is complementary.",
